Halve, peel and chop the @Echalion Shallot{1%small} into ½cm pieces. Trim the root and the dark green leafy part from the @Leek{1}. Halve lengthways and thinly slice widthways. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Chop the bottom 2cm off the @Asparagus{200%g} and discard. Cut the spears in half widthways (see pic). Roughly chop the @Flat Leaf Parsley{1} (stalks and all). Halve the @Lemon{1/2}.

Boil the @Water for the Risotto{750%ml} in a #saucepan{} over high heat. Add the @KNORR Vegetable Stock{1%pot}, stir to dissolve and reduce the heat to low. Heat a glug of @oil{} in a wide bottomed saucepan on medium heat. Add the shallot and leek. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and cook until soft, ~{5-6%minutes}. Add the garlic, stir together and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Pour in the @Arborio Rice{175%g} and stir together. Cook for ~{1%minute} so the rice is coated in the garlicky oil. Add the @White Wine Vinegar{12%ml} and allow it to evaporate. Stir in a ladle of stock and when the stock has been absorbed by the rice, add another ladle of stock. Keep the pan on medium heat and continue stirring and adding stock. Tip: Let the rice absorb the stock before adding another ladle. This should take ~{20-25%minutes}.

Halfway through the risotto cooking time, heat a splash of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} over medium-high heat. Stir-fry the asparagus until it has a little colour, ~{2%minutes}, then add a splash of @water{} to the pan, cover with a #lid{} or some #kitchen foil{} and leave to steam until tender, ~{3-5%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and transfer to a #plate{}. Keep warm covered with foil.

Leave the pan on the heat (and add a little @oil{} if the pan is dry). Add the @King Prawns{150%g} and stir-fry until cooked, ~{4-5%minutes}. IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the centre. When cooked, remove from the heat and add a squeeze of lemon juice. Sprinkle on half the parsley with all of the @Dukkah Mix{2%tbsp} and stir together.

When your risotto is cooked, remove from the heat and add the @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{40%g}, @Unsalted Butter{30%g} and the remaining parsley. Stir well to make the risotto really creamy. Taste and add more salt, pepper and lemon juice to taste. Spoon the risotto into your #bowls{} and top with the dukkah prawns and asparagus pieces. Enjoy!